
*******************************************************************************
macrocp		- 	copy a user macro file 
macrosyscp	- 	copy a system macro file to a user macro file
*******************************************************************************

  The macrocp command copies user macro files from the user's macro
  file directory to the user's macro file directory.  
  The macrosyscp command copies system macro files from the system's macro
  file directory to the user's macro file directory.  

  The macrocp allows a user to make a copy of an existing macro in
  the users's macro directory.  The macrosyscp allows a user to make
  a copy of a system macro and place the copy in the users macro
  directory.  This allows the user to modify system macros for the users
  own use.

  Usage  -  macrocp('fromfile','tofile')
  	    macrosyscp('fromfile','tofile')


  Examples:
       macrocp('dan','rick')	     make a copy of user macro dan, name 
				     it rick.
       macrosyscp('rene','greg')     copy system macro rene into a user
				     macro named greg.
